      <div id="faq" class="tab-pane fade">

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>What if I don’t want to speak?</p>
            <p>Learning a foreign language requires you to speak in order to develop fluency in it. Though it might be embarrassing to start with, it is a necessary part of the learning process. If you are unwilling to speak at all, then this language learning course is not likely to be for you.</p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>Will I learn how to write in Chinese?</p>
            <p>For the sake of the bootcamp and its limited timeframe, the focus is on how to converse in the language orally. Most Chinese natives rarely write and mostly type, hence the ability to learn to write in Chinese will be developed through typing the language on a computer - this will be taught during the course. If there are learners who wish to practice/learn writing by hand, additional resources will be provided.</p>
          </li>

